            <title>[HBASE-1088] how to HBase 0.18.1 run on Hadoop 0.19.0</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1088</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Hadoop 0.19 refactored all of the DFS classes. As a result,HBase 0.18 will not run on Hadoop 0.19 unless the source is modified and recompiled.&lt;br/&gt;
I modied the source and recompiled.&lt;br/&gt;
the test result is ok.&lt;br/&gt;
The modied source is appended  as patch. the compiled hadoop-0.18.1.jar is appended.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;you should do the following&lt;br/&gt;
method1(with patch):&lt;br/&gt;
1.download the patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1088&quot; title=&quot;how to HBase 0.18.1 run on Hadoop 0.19.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1088&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1088&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.txt.0.18.1 from the attachfile into $HBASE_HOME&lt;br/&gt;
2.execute patch command in $HBASE_HOME&lt;br/&gt;
      patch &amp;lt; &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1088&quot; title=&quot;how to HBase 0.18.1 run on Hadoop 0.19.0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HBASE-1088&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HBASE-1088&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.txt.0.18.1&lt;br/&gt;
3.execute ant in $HBASE_HOME for build&lt;br/&gt;
     ant&lt;br/&gt;
4.if step 3 is ok,copy $HBASE_HOME/build/hbase-0.18.1.jar into $HBASE_HOME&lt;br/&gt;
5.delete the $HBASE_HOME/lib/hadoop-0.18.1-core.jar and hadoop-0.18.1-test.jar&lt;br/&gt;
6.copy hadoop-0.19.0-core.jar and hadoop-0.19.0-test.jar into $HBASE_HOME/lib from $HADOOP_HOME&lt;br/&gt;
7.restart hbase&lt;br/&gt;
done &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;method2(with jar file):&lt;br/&gt;
1.download the hbase-0.18.1.jar from the attachfile into $HBASE_HOME&lt;br/&gt;
2.delete the $HBASE_HOME/lib/hadoop-0.18.1-core.jar and hadoop-0.18.1-test.jar&lt;br/&gt;
3.copy hadoop-0.19.0-core.jar and hadoop-0.19.0-test.jar into $HBASE_HOME/lib&lt;br/&gt;
4.restart hbase&lt;br/&gt;
done&lt;/p&gt;</description>
